# Git branch naming

Working branches: `<type>/<short-description>` (`feat`/`fix`/`hotfix`/`chore`/`refactor`/`docs`/`test`/`ci`/`build`/`perf`). Single trunk: `main` is the only long-lived branch. Hotfixes are ordinary short-lived `fix/*` (or `hotfix/*`) branches that fix-forward to `main` — there is no protected `release/*` branch. `claude/*` is reserved for AI web sessions. Enforced by `.husky/pre-push` (owner: **[code-quality-guard](../skills/code-quality-guard/SKILL.md)**).
